MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write|Agent
MATCH_PATTERN: (arcade.*spec|arcade.*design|arcade.*plan|new.*game.*cartridge|batch.*arcade)
ADVISORY: |
  When writing or reviewing an arcade game spec/plan, verify ALL integration
  points are explicitly addressed. Specs consistently miss items from this list:

  REQUIRED (8 registration touchpoints):
  1. GameTypeSchema in packages/shared-types/src/index.ts
  2. GAME_TYPE_INFO in packages/shared-types/src/game-type-info.ts (name + description)
  3. Config.game.<name> in packages/shared-types/src/config.ts (timeLimitMs + reward divisors)
  4. GAME_POOL in packages/shared-types/src/cycle-defaults.ts (minPlayers + array position)
  5. Machine file in packages/game-cartridges/src/machines/<name>.ts
  6. GAME_REGISTRY in packages/game-cartridges/src/machines/index.ts
  7. GAME_COMPONENTS in apps/client/src/components/panels/GamePanel.tsx (lazy import)
  8. GAME_STAT_CONFIG in apps/client/src/cartridges/games/shared/Leaderboard.tsx

  COMMONLY MISSED:
  - LIVE_GAMES exclusion (confirm NOT in set — solo arcade games are never live)
  - Event factory confirmation (Events.Game.start/result work for new types without registration)
  - DemoServer impact check (apps/game-server/src/demo/)
  - renderBreakdown prop on wrapper component
  - GAME_STAT_CONFIG should use a distinctive stat, not generic "score"
  - Result payload values must be integers (arcade machine floors everything)
  - timeElapsed is server-injected — client must NOT send it in onResult
